{"article_id":"aiR7iWKUcN1XM5jQ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Tropical Storm Florence weakened to a tropical depression early Sunday ,","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"but significant portions of North and South Carolina were expected to remain vulnerable to flash flooding and major river flooding ,","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"forecasters said .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"The further downgrading of what had been a powerful hurricane several days ago","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"came in a 5 a.m . ET Sunday advisory from the National Hurricane Center .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"With the update , the NHC also announced","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"that a tropical storm warning","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"stretching from South Santee River , S.C. , to Surf City , N.C. ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"had been discontinued ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"and that no coastal watches or warnings remained in effect .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"On Saturday , officials in South Carolina confirmed the state ' s first fatality from Florence ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"bringing the region-wide death toll from the storm to at least 11","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"-- though the News & Observer in Raleigh , N.C. , was reporting at least 14 deaths .","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"Police said","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"a 62-year-old woman was killed late Friday","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"when the vehicle","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"she was driving","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"struck a tree","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"that had fallen across Highway 18 near the town of Union .","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"Capt . Kelly Hughes of the South Carolina Highway Patrol said","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"the woman ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"who was wearing a seat belt ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"died at the scene","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"and no passengers were in the vehicle at the time .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"A mother and her 8-month old child were among the first confirmed dead","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"after a massive tree crushed their brick home in Wilmington , North Carolina on Friday .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"Another man , 81 , died Friday","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"while trying to evacuate Wayne County , North Carolina ,","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"and a husband and wife were killed in a house fire ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"according to the medical examiner ' s office .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"Lenoir County spokesman Bryan Hanks said","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"a 78-year-old man was electrocuted in the rain","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"while trying to connect extension cords for a generator","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"and that another man , 77 , died","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"after he went outside","depth":15},{"id":35,"text":"to check on his hunting dogs","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"and was blown down .","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"Duplin County Sheriff ' s Office confirmed three more deaths due to \" flash flooding and swift water on roadways . \"","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"Authorities in North Carolina have confirmed 10 deaths so far .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"Early Saturday , the state tally fluctuated","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"when officials initially counted ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"then subtracted , two deaths","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"now thought to have been the result of a murder-suicide during the storm .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"That case is under investigation .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Mandatory evacuations were issued for areas","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"surrounding the banks of Cape Fear River in North Carolina .","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"The National Hurricane Center said on Saturday afternoon","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"that \" catastrophic flooding \" is expected in certain parts of the Carolinas .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"Florence parked itself over the Carolinas on Saturday ,","depth":5},{"id":49,"text":"bringing with it torrential downpours , dangerous winds and coastal flooding","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"that required hundreds of water rescues","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"and ended in multiple deaths .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"`` It 's like being stalked by a turtle , ''","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"FEMA associate director Jeffrey Byard said about the slow-moving storm .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"`` There 's a lot of rain","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"to come .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"There 's a lot of rain","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"that 's fallen . ''","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"Emergency workers have been going door to door in North Carolina ,","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"pleading with people","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"who have chosen to ride out the storm","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"to leave .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"\" I can not overstate it :","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Floodwaters are rising ,","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"and","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"if you aren ' t watching for them ,","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"you are risking your life , \"","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"North Carolina Gov . Roy Cooper said Saturday .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"More than 2 feet of rain over the course of 24 hours has fallen in some places in North Carolina ,","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"with forecasters calling for an additional 11⁄2 feet by the end of the weekend .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"The fear is that flash flooding could devastate communities ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"endanger dams","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"and block bridges .","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"The storm also knocked out power to nearly a million people .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"SHIRTLESS MAN STARES DOWN HURRICANE WITH FLAG IN HAND :","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"'JUST BEING FREE AND AMERICAN '","depth":6},{"id":76,"text":"Aerial photos along the coast near New Bern showed homes","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"floating in water","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"and rescuers","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"racing to reach the people","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"who were trapped inside .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"Cooper called Florence an \" uninvited brute \"","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"that could wipe out entire communities","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"as it grinds its way across land .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"\" The fact is , this storm is deadly","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"and we know","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"we are days away from an ending , \"","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"Since Thursday , more than 360 people have been carried to higher ground amid rising waters from a river","depth":4},{"id":89,"text":"swelled by both rain and salty storm surge .","depth":4},{"id":90,"text":"New Bern , North Carolina , Mayor Dana Outlaw urged residents not to return just yet .","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"`` We have a lot of downed power lines , ''","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"he told Fox News .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"`` We 're very concerned with these energized lines","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"and folks could get hurt .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"So give the city time","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"to get out","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"and assess our infrastructure","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"and get the roads safe","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"for you to travel . ''","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"Shaken","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"after seeing waves crashing on the Neuse River just outside his house in New Bern ,","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"restaurant owner and hurricane veteran Tom Ballance wished","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"he had evacuated .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"`` I feel like the dumbest human being","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"who ever walked the face of the earth , ''","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"Since its roared ashore ,","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"Florence has flattened trees ,","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"buckled buildings","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"and crumpled roads .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"Storm surges","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"-- the bulge of ocean water","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"pushed ashore by the hurricane --","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"were as high as 10 feet .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"Florence peaked at a Category 4 with top winds of 140 mph over warm ocean water","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"before making landfall as a Category 1 .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"It blew ashore along a mostly boarded-up , emptied-out stretch of coastline .","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"By midmorning Saturday , Florence lazily inched its way about 40 miles west of Myrtle Beach , South Carolina at 2 mph","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"- slower","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"than most humans walk .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"`` It 's like being stalked by a turtle , ''","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"FEMA associate director Jeffrey Byard said about the slow-moving storm .","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"`` There 's a lot of rain","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"to come .","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"There 's a lot of rain","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"that 's fallen . ''","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"South Carolina Rep. Tom Rice described the storm to Fox News as a \" slow poison . \"","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"Florence ' s devastation has less to do with wind","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"and more to do with water .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"Morehead City , North Carolina , had received 23 inches of rain by Friday night ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"and forecasters warned Saturday morning","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"that parts of the Carolinas could get up to 15 inches more .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"WEATHER CHANNEL DEFENDS REPORTER CAPTURED SWAYING IN FLORENCE WINDS","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"AS 2 PEOPLE WALK BEHIND HIM","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"At times , Florence was moving forward no faster","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"than a human can walk ,","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"and it has remained such a wide storm","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"that its counter-clockwise winds keep scooping up massive amounts of moisture from the sea .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"The flooding began on barrier islands in North Carolina","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"and then spread into coastal and river communities there and in South Carolina ,","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"swamping the white sands and golf courses in North Myrtle Beach .","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"For people","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"living inland in the Carolinas ,","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"maximum peril could come days later","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"as all that water drains ,","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"overflowing rivers","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"and causing flash floods .","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"Authorities warned , too , of risks of mudslides and environmental disasters from floodwaters","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"washing over industrial waste sites and hog farms .","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"About 9,700 National Guard troops and civilians were deployed with high-water vehicles , helicopters and boats .","depth":6},{"id":151,"text":"Florence could become a major test for the Federal Emergency Management Agency ,","depth":7},{"id":152,"text":"which was heavily criticized as slow and unprepared last year for Hurricane Maria in Puerto Rico ,","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"where the death toll was put at nearly 3,000 .","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"The hurricane center said","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"the storm will eventually break up over the southern Appalachians","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"and make a right hook to the northeast ,","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"its rainy remnants moving into the Mid-Atlantic states and New England by the middle of next week .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"Meteorologist Ryan Maue , of weathermodels.com , calculated","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"that Florence could dump a staggering 18 trillion gallons of rain over a week on North Carolina , South Carolina , Virginia , Georgia , Tennessee , Kentucky and Maryland .","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"That 's enough","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"to fill the Chesapeake Bay","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"or cover the entire state of Texas with nearly 4 inches of water .","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"US COAST GUARD MEMBER ' REMOVED '","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"AFTER MAKING ' OFFENSIVE '","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"OK SIGN ON LIVE TV","depth":7},{"id":166,"text":"North Carolina alone is forecast to get 9.6 trillion gallons , enough","depth":7},{"id":167,"text":"to cover the Tar Heel state to a depth of about 10 inches .","depth":7},{"id":168,"text":"In Jacksonville , North Carolina , next to Camp Lejeune , firefighters and police fought wind and rain","depth":7},{"id":169,"text":"as they went door to door","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"to pull more than 60 people out","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"as the Triangle Motor Inn began to crumble .","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"In New Bern , population 29,000 , flooding on the Neuse River left 500 people in peril .","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"Ashley Warren and boyfriend Chris Smith managed to paddle away from their home in a boat with their two dogs","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"and were left shaken .","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"`` Honestly , I grew up in Wilmington .","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"I love hurricanes .","depth":11},{"id":177,"text":"But this one has been an experience for me , ''","depth":10},{"id":178,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"`` We might leave . ''","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":359,"left":253,"right":358,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":253,"left":223,"right":252,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":223,"left":189,"right":222,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":184,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":